commit.title: Refresh Set when defining evars up to cumulativity, flexibly.
commit.message:
Refresh Set when defining evars up to cumulativity, flexibly.

Before, we solved a problem `Set <= ?X` by `X := Set`, which is less
general than `X := Type@{i}, Set <= i` for a flexible `i` which can
be collapsed to `Set`.

Changes to test-suite:

In bug_3281.v, we can now check `(nat = Set)`.
In bug_5280.v, we get rid of a universe parameter which was constrained
to be equal to U.
In polymorphism.v, the lemma trans_co_eq_inv_arrow_morphism now has two
fewer universe parameters by noting that the two types passed to arrow
have the same level (both are applied R).

Change to refman:

Remove section: Interaction with subtyping.
The documented unexpected behavior no longer occurs.
Maybe merits a CHANGES entry?
